This paper is about regularized empirical risk minimization (R-ERM) in machine learning, which is a topic closely related to the sub-category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper proposes asynchronous stochastic proximal optimization algorithms with variance reduction, which involves optimization techniques and parallel computing, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-categories of "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC) and "Numerical Analysis" (cs.NA). The paper also mentions the use of block partitions, which is a common technique in the sub-category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that demonstrate the practical efficiency of the proposed algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) where the focus is on analyzing large-scale data sets.
